text: public announcement: there seems to be no fix to this issue, and not sure when nintendo is planning on fixing the issue or if they even are aware of it or worst of all if there is a fix to it even possible, just wanted to let more people know, that there is an issue popping up on the game and it seems to be happening to a lot of people and it's completely random with no warning it can happen whether you have the digital version or the physical version of the game, it's the issue where all of a sudden without warning a screen will pop up saying something like "There was an error in the system" or something like that and then the damn game will crash knocking you back to the title screen and when you load you'll have lost everything since the last time you've saved your game, so this is a warning to all please please please save and save very VERY often, especially if you've caught a rare or hard to catch pokemon or you've been out collecting items and such[or those  blue flames] because if you don't save and this happens you'll have to start over and collect the stuff all over again[except with mine, i got lucky and found a seed of mastery and two rare candies and a blue flame and had collected quite a few items, good items, and then all of a sudden without warning i got the message and it crashed and i lost everything, worst thing is the seed of mastery and rare candies are not where i found them, or i forgot where they were i dunno but now there gone and everything else is gone......daaaaamn iiiiiiiiit alllllllllll] i've already clocked in 121"29 hours on the game and i've had at least 5 or 6 of those crashes so far, so now i save every couple of minutes or so or even save right after i collected a bunch of stuff especially if there good stuff or catch rare or hard to catch pokemon....cause sadly there is no warning, no rhyme or reason, just BAM your crashed, so SAVE VERY OFTEN, because there is no actual fix or patch to this issue[not yet but hopefully they'll fix it or patch it somehow]
